description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Clinical Research Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – The Fritchie Research Unit, Cheltenham&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary –£24,907 to £30,615 per annum (Band 5)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 37.5 (part-time considered dependent upon operational requirements)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 x Fixed Term contract/secondment opportunity until end of March 2022&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal applicants who wish to be considered for a secondment opportunity should discuss with their line manager the suitability of a possible secondment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Gloucestershire Health and Care NHS Foundation Trust Research Team has a vacancy for a Band 5 Clinical Research Practitioner to work half-time on the TACK Research Trial and half-time on other National Institute for Health Research studies. The TACK study is a cluster randomised controlled trial testing a technology-supported and solution-focused intervention (DIALOG+) for people with chronic depression.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role represents an opportunity for someone seeking career or personal development by trying out their skills in the research environment. It also provides the opportunity to work with a Nursing Times Award Finalist team, delivering on our vision to be world-class centre of practice-based research and development, to help make life better.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be a highly organised, innovative and enthusiastic individual to assist the Research Team in delivering research to patients, carers and staff.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who might you be? We would be interested to hear from you if you are a dedicated nurse, psychology-based practitioner or allied healthcare professional, willing to learn new skills as a research practitioner and locally co-ordinate research studies. If you have previously supported Quality Improvement, audits, CEQUINs or service evaluations you could have transferable skills to join our friendly, flexible research team. If you do not have direct NHS research experience, full training and mentoring can be provided for the right candidate.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based at the Trust’s purpose-built Research Unit in Cheltenham, you will be part of a team which supports all aspects of our research activity in the Trust, including feasibility of research studies, setting trials up and data collection. You will be required to travel countywide to deliver research in across all areas of our services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for the right person to join our friendly team who is able to understand project management, research protocols and the requirements of local or national research regulations. You will need to have excellent personal and communication skills, as you will be working with patients, carers, internal and external customers, and may be required to travel to local or national meetings.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Mark Walker, Head of Research and Development, on 01242 634491 or email mark.walker@ghc.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need, therefore we support staff to relocate with our relocation policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘ Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
